<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="22" type="generic diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="22">Generic diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="22">
<taxonomicName authority="Habeeb, 1974" authorityName="Habeeb" authorityYear="1974" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Debsacarus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Debsacarus" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Debsacarus</taxonomicName>
differ from all other 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="9" pageNumber="22" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Testudacarinae">Testudacarinae</taxonomicName>
in having four-segmented pedipalps (instead of five) and projections on the anterio-tips of coxae-I. With the exception of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Testudacarus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Testudacarus hyporhynchus" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hyporhynchus">Testudacarus hyporhynchus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Habeeb, 1974" authorityName="Habeeb" authorityYear="1974" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Debsacarus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Debsacarus" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Debsacarus</taxonomicName>
differ from all other 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="9" pageNumber="22" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Testudacarinae">Testudacarinae</taxonomicName>
in having an elongate gnathosoma and an extremely narrow gnathosomal bay that is covered dorsally and ends anterior to the leg-I insertion ventrally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="22" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="22">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="22">Known from only two counties (Los Angeles and Monterey) in California.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
